# React Component Patterns

## Component Structure
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — typed functional component
const UserCard: React.FC<UserCardProps> = ({ name, age }) => {
  const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false); // local UI state only
  return <View>...</View>;
};

// ❌ BAD — class component
class UserCard extends React.Component { ... }
```

## Styling
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — StyleSheet.create for performance
const styles = StyleSheet.create({ container: { flex: 1 } });

// ❌ BAD — inline style object created every render
<View style={{ flex: 1, padding: 20 }} />
```

- Use theme constants from `src/Constants/theme.ts` for colors and typography.
- Place `StyleSheet.create(...)` at the **bottom** of the file, after `export default`.

## Comments
- Explain **why**, not what. Code should be self-documenting.
- Use JSDoc for complex utility functions.
